title.narrative: To reduce HIV infections by 75%, new HIV infections among children by <5%, AIDS related deaths by 70% and Stigma and Discrimination to 13.8%, all by 2023.

description.narrative: Tanzania (United Republic) - HIV - Ministry of Finance and Planning of the United Republic of Tanzania - MOFP. This program has the following goals: To increase coverage of HIV and AIDS services in general population and sub-populations to ensure that by 2020, 90% of people living with HIV knows their status, 90% of all people diagnosed with HIV are enrolled, followed and receive timely and efficacious highly active antiretroviral therapy, and 90% of all people receiving the antiretroviral therapy will attain sustainable viral suppression.. The objectives of this program are: 90% of people living with HIV knows their status by 2020. 90% of all people diagnosed with HIV are enrolled, followed and receive timely and efficacious highly active antiretroviral therapy by 2020. 90% of all people receiving the antiretroviral therapy will attain sustainable viral suppression by 2020
